Sentencas: Anodic performance and power generating properties of the cell using various oxide composites consisting of Mn, Fe co-doped CeO2 and perovskite oxide were investigated by using La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.15Co0.05O3 electrolyte.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte

Sentencas: It was found that the theoretical open circuit voltage and reasonably high power density were achieved on the cell using oxide composites consisting of Ce(Mn,Fe)O-2-La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O-3 for anode.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte

Sentencas: The maximum power density was achieved for values of similar to 1.0, 0.3, and 0.05 W/cm(2) at 1273, 1073, and 873 K, respectively.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte

Sentencas: Oxidation tolerance was also studied and it was found that the power density was slightly improved after exposure to reoxidation treatment.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte

Sentencas: This study demonstrated that the cell using CeO2 and LaFeO3 based oxide composite for anode is highly tolerant against reoxidation treatment.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte

Sentencas: An increase in in the power density by reoxidation treatment was observed and this could be attributed to the improved contact of Ce(Mn,Fe)O-2-La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O-3 composite powder.
Titulo: Oxide Composite of Ce(Mn,Fe)O2 and La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O3 for Anode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using LaGaO3 Electrolyte
